## Error Diagnosis

The error is:

```
keyword div(phiv,hU) is undefined in dictionary ".../system/fvSchemes/divSchemes"
```

The `shallowWaterFoam` solver requires the divergence scheme `div(phiv,hU)`, but the current `fvSchemes` file only defines `div(phiCorr,hU)` and `div(phi,hU)`. It does not define `div(phiv,hU)`.

In `shallowWaterFoam`, the flux variable is named `phiv` (velocity-based flux) rather than `phi` (volume-based flux). The solver internally constructs the convection term using `div(phiv,hU)` and needs to find this entry in the `divSchemes` sub-dictionary.

## Solution

Add the missing `div(phiv,hU)` entry to the `divSchemes` sub-dictionary in `system/fvSchemes`. There are two approaches:

**Option 1:** Add `div(phiv,hU)` alongside the existing divergence schemes. For example, append/modify the `divSchemes` section to include:

```
divSchemes
{
    default         none;
    div(phiv,hU)    Gauss linear;
    div(phiCorr,hU) Gauss linear;
    div(phi,hU)     Gauss linear;
}
```

**Option 2:** Set `default` to `Gauss linear` instead of `none`, which would catch any other divergence terms the solver might need:

```
divSchemes
{
    default         Gauss linear;
    div(phiCorr,hU) Gauss linear;
    div(phi,hU)     Gauss linear;
}
```

Either approach will resolve the error. Option 1 is more explicit and conservative, ensuring only the known-needed terms are defined. After adding the missing keyword, re-run `shallowWaterFoam`.

